ksdk:manifest.name: SDK version 2.4.2 package for FRDM-K64F board
ksdk:manifest.brief: This is SDK version 2.4.2 manifest file. It describes the content of the SDK version 2.4.2 package for FRDM-K64F board and additional settings for tools that support SDK version 2.4.2

board.name: FRDM-K64F-OM13588
board.description: USB Type-C Shield Board for Kinetis Freedom Board

specific.content: The USB Type-C shield board combined with a Kinetis Power Delivery SDK allows a system designer to tether a USB Type-C connector to any Kinetis development platform.

board.name: FRDM-K64F-AGM04
board.description: Sensor Toolbox Development Platform for MMA8652, FXAS21002, and MAG3110 9-Axis Solution

specific.content:
This is your ecosystem for the NXP MMA8652 accelerometer, FXAS21002 gyro, and MAG3110 magnetometer providing a 9-axis solution. This includes Demo Kit, Sensor Shield Development Board and Breakout Board. Each of these boards is supported by NXP Software: Sensor Toolbox – CE and ISSDK.
  • The Demo Kit (FRDM-K64F-AGM04) enables a demonstration using ISSDK and Sensor Toolbox – CE.
  • The Sensor Shield Development Board (FRDM-STBC-AGM04) enables evaluation and development. The Sensor Shield Development board is compatible with most NXP Freedom development boards.
  • The Breakout Board (BRKT-STBC-AGM04) enables prototyping of your sensor designs.

board.name: FRDM-K64F-AGM01
board.description: Sensor Toolbox Development Platform for FXAS21002C and FXOS8700C 9-Axis Solution

specific.content:
Demonstration Kits (FRDMSTBC-AGM01 Sensor Shield Development Board with FRDM-K64F Board):
  • Enables an ‘Out of the box’ Sensor Fusion demo using the NXP Sensor Toolbox Ecosystem.
  • Enables quick and easy visualization of 9-Axis (3 Axis Gyroscope + 6-Axis E-compass) sensor data and results.

board.name: FRDM-K64F-MULT2B
board.description: FRDM-FXS-MULT2-B: FRDM-FXS-MULT2-B: Freedom Development Platform for NXP® Sensors with Bluetooth®

specific.content: The FRDM-FXS-MULT2-B is a sensor expansion board enabling NXP® Sensor Fusion using the MMA8652FC 3-axis accelerometer, FXLS8471Q 3-axis accelerometer, MAG3110 3-axis magnetometer, FXAS21002C 3-axis gyroscope, MPL3115A2 pressure sensor, FXOS8700CQ 3-axis accelerometer plus a 3 axis magnetometer and the MMA9553L sensing platform. The FRDM-FXS-MULT2-B offers 12-axis sensing, wireless communication via Bluetooth and the compatible Android™ app, the NXP Sensor Fusion Toolbox. The board is also supported by the ISSDK.

board.name: FRDM-K64F
board.description: FRDM-K64F: Freedom Development Platform for Kinetis K64, K63, and K24 MCUs

specific.content:
The Freedom-K64F is an ultra-low-cost development platform for Kinetis K64, K63, and K24 MCUs
  • Form-factor compatible with the Arduino R3 pin layout
  • Peripherals enable rapid prototyping, including a 6-axis digital accelerometer and magnetometer to create full eCompass capabilities, a tri-colored LED and 2 user push-buttons for direct interaction, a microSD card slot, and connectivity using onboard Ethernet port and headers for use with Bluetooth® and 2.4 GHz radio add-on modules
  • OpenSDAv2, the NXP open source hardware embedded serial and debug adapter running an open source bootloader, offers options for serial communication, flash programming, and run-control debugging

device.name: MK64F12
device.description: K64_120: Kinetis® K64-120 MHz, 256KB SRAM Microcontrollers (MCUs) based on ARM® Cortex®-M4 Core

specific.content:
The Kinetis K series MCU portfolio offers the broadest selection of pin, peripheral- and software-compatible MCU families based on the ARM® Cortex®-M4 core. The Kinetis K64 120 MHz MCUs feature:
  • IEEE® 1588 Ethernet MCUs
  • Optimization for applications requiring large memory densities and low-power processing efficiency
  • Crystal-less USB design for reduced system cost and board space
  • The comprehensive enablement and scalability of the Kinetis portfolio
